p:
The objectives of transmission control are as follows:


   •

to prevent infection;


   •

to treat early so as to avoid severe complications;


   •

to provide prophylaxis to those exposed to infection so as to prevent them from developing the disease or reduce its severity;


   •

if a vaccine is available, to enhance the population's immunity to the virus in order to reduce disease and death and to stop or significantly slow the spread of the disease;


   •

to allow the lifting of all distancing measures.
